<subSubSection id="D106E0211689F5CBA15D10ACA0BADAA0" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A517887542533ECA4C2B5FA32ECA183F" pageId="0" pageNumber="609">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="95F0E6FB624373661500662A1A8E1198" pageId="0" pageNumber="609">
2.35 mm (n = 1), 3.36 
<normalizedToken id="ABEA9D5768F6F66AC9F0FB57D63B24ED" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the elytral apex attenuate and strongly emarginate, declivity convex, declivital interstriae 2 denticulate, elytral apex with interstriae 3 and 9 joining, forming a smooth continuous carina that continues submarginally to apex, apex produced, declivital interstriae 3 denticles much larger than those of interstriae 1, and interstriae with short erect bristle-like setae that are at least twice as wide as interstrial width.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
